                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, irregular</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda Mikāʾel. Walda Mikāʾel
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the concluding supplication formula on <locus target="#28rb">28rb</locus> and in the supplications on <locus target="#6va">6va</locus>, 34va. 
 
 Probably the same scribe
                        produced mss. AGM-005, AP-028, AP-047 and MA-002.<date>19th century
                           (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰላ:</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም: </expan> (<locus target="#29v">29v</locus>, 32rv, 33r)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; two initial lines of the incipit of
                           Text II; two initial lines of sections of Texts I-2 and I-3; the words
                           salām “salutation”, sǝbḥat “glory” and a few others in Text II; elements
                           of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 A few
                           groups of lines (alternating with black lines) on the incipit page of
                           Text I.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#26r">26r</locus> (incipit of Text I-1): simple uncoloured
                        ornamental band; geometric motifs.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
